quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  50,22,"(It will be said to the sinners): "
  50,23,"And his companion (angel) will say: "
  50,24,"(Allah will say to the angels): "
  51,16,"Taking joy in the things which their Lord has given them. Verily, they were before this Muhsinûn (good-doers. See V.2:112)."
  51,17,"They used to sleep but little by night [invoking their Lord (Allâh) and praying, with fear and hope]."
  51,18,"And in the hours before dawn, they were (found) asking (Allâh) for forgiveness."
  52,7,"Verily, the Torment of your Lord will surely come to pass."
  52,8,"There is none that can avert it."
  52,9,"On the Day when the heaven will shake with a dreadful shaking,"
  53,1,"By the star when it goes down (or vanishes)."
  53,2,"Your companion (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) has neither gone astray nor has erred."
  53,3,"Nor does he speak of (his own) desire."